maaaaaaaaaaaannnnnnnn look. My best friend is getting married in 30 minutes and I can‚Äôt contain my excitement. I‚Äôve been thru so much with this guy. Running from cops in Littleton, working on lawns with Pat, Tavern 356, tragic deaths, we been thru it all. I‚Äôm so happy for you. Im so proud of you. I know you‚Äôll be the best husband, father and partner. You got a good one here Meg!

Happy Birthday to my young prince. I‚Äôm so thankful to be your dad. To watch you learn, grow and live is the biggest blessing. You are sweet, kind and thoughtful. You‚Äôre funny and passionate. You‚Äôre my favorite 6 year old. Happy Birthday Bubba!!!

Today is a day I think we should celebrate. We should dance and eat macaroons. We should wear our favorite outfit and enjoy vodka soda‚Äôs with 5 limes. Today is one of my favorite people‚Äôs birthday. Today is Mallory‚Äôs day. It‚Äôs been 1 year and 1 week since she passed and I couldn‚Äôt begin to describe how missed she is. Her impact and influence on me, my son and the world is unmatched. Everyday I try to make her proud and keep the promises I made to her. Every day I use lessons I learned with her, wisdoms she shared and try to live life like she would. That means handling everything with grace, never giving up, oh and not smoking cigs. I love you MalFresh, thank you for everything you‚Äôve done for me and my son.

this time last year we were getting ready for your birthday dinner at Tag. It was an intimate dinner; your parents your aunt your brother and I. I remember you were so excited for the pop rocks dish they had. It was a great dinner. Your mom said a toast; it was a tough year but we were looking forward to the next one. None of us could imagine being here today.
I don't know how to feel today. I know that you would want today to be about celebrating rather than mourning. So that's what we will do. Today is not your memorial service; it's your birthday party. All your friends are coming. And we'll dance, smile and laugh in your name.

Two of my best friends are getting married today. I couldn‚Äôt be more excited. I couldn‚Äôt be happier. I love these guys and I love their relationship. this post is for the two people in this world I couldn't live without, the two people I'd die for, the two people that give me life.

25 years ago TODAY I walked into a hospital room to meet my brother for the first time. I was just as excited to meet you then as I am to hangout and watch football today. You've been through so much yet you persevered. Today you're 25 and living the life you wanted for yourself when you were 15. You're the man.

5 days ago was my son Paxton's birthday. He turned 4. He is the light of my world. I'm so thankful to be his father. He's such an amazing kid and he makes me so proud. I'm so excited to watch you grow. I'll be there to cheer and help with every step. Love you bubba.

I remember when The Carter 3 came out. I woke up at like 8 AM and drove to your house. We drove around listening to Lil Wayne's greatness and smoking "PrimeTimes." That was 10 years ago and really ain't nothin changed but the address.
happy birthday brother.

So many things I want to say. So little time. I'm so happy you're not hurting anymore. I'm so glad you're at peace. As much as this hurts I'm so thankful to have just known you. Much less be loved by you. You're the best person I've ever known. That's not a stretch or fantasy I've made up. You are the best person I've ever known. Thank you for being you. All I can say is thank you. You brightened the world and my life. You brightened the lives of people I introduced you to. You've shaped me as much as any family member or friend. I'm not ready to live life without you. Even when we hit our rough patch we talked everyday. We were each other's person. You showed me a love that I truly didn't know was possible. A feeling I didn't know existed. Genuinely a whole new world. I'm sad because you're gone but eternally grateful to have be blessed by presence and grace.
Rest In Peace Mal. I love you.
